    • Enum Constant Detail

      • Explore

        public static final PlacerDirective Explore
        Increased placer effort in detail placement and post-placement optimization.

      • EarlyBlockPlacement

        public static final PlacerDirective EarlyBlockPlacement
        Timing-driven placement of RAM and DSP blocks. The RAM and DSP block locations are finalized early in the placement process and are used as anchors to place the remaining logic.

      • WLDrivenBlockPlacement

        public static final PlacerDirective WLDrivenBlockPlacement
        Wire length-driven placement of RAM and DSP blocks. Override timing-driven placement by directing the Vivado placer to minimize the distance of connections to and from blocks.

      • ExtraNetDelay_high

        public static final PlacerDirective ExtraNetDelay_high
        Increases estimated delay of high fanout and long-distance nets. Three levels of pessimism are supported: high, medium, and low. ExtraNetDelay_high applies the highest level of pessimism.

      • ExtraNetDelay_low

        public static final PlacerDirective ExtraNetDelay_low
        Increases estimated delay of high fanout and long-distance nets. Three levels of pessimism are supported: high, medium, and low. ExtraNetDelay_low applies the lowest level of pessimism.

      • AltSpreadLogic_high

        public static final PlacerDirective AltSpreadLogic_high
        Spreads logic throughout the device to avoid creating congested regions. Three levels are supported: high, medium, and low. AltSpreadLogic_high achieves the highest level of spreading.

      • AltSpreadLogic_medium

        public static final PlacerDirective AltSpreadLogic_medium
        Spreads logic throughout the device to avoid creating congested regions. Three levels are supported: high, medium, and low. AltSpreadLogic_medium achieves a medium level of spreading compared to low and high.

      • AltSpreadLogic_low

        public static final PlacerDirective AltSpreadLogic_low
        Spreads logic throughout the device to avoid creating congested regions. Three levels are supported: high, medium, and low. AltSpreadLogic_low achieves the lowest level of spreading.

      • ExtraPostPlacementOpt

        public static final PlacerDirective ExtraPostPlacementOpt
        Increased placer effort in post-placement optimization.

      • ExtraTimingOpt

        public static final PlacerDirective ExtraTimingOpt
        Use an alternate algorithm for timing-driven placement with greater effort for timing.

      • SSI_SpreadLogic_high

        public static final PlacerDirective SSI_SpreadLogic_high
        Distribute logic across SLRs. SSI_SpreadLogic_high achieves the highest level of distribution.

      • SSI_SpreadLogic_low

        public static final PlacerDirective SSI_SpreadLogic_low
        Distribute logic across SLRs. SSI_SpreadLogic_low achieves a minimum level of logic distribution, while reducing placement runtime.

      • SSI_SpreadSLLs

        public static final PlacerDirective SSI_SpreadSLLs
        Partition across SLRs and allocate extra area for regions of higher connectivity.

      • SSI_BalanceSLLs

        public static final PlacerDirective SSI_BalanceSLLs
        Partition across SLRs while attempting to balance SLLs between SLRs.

      • SSI_BalanceSLRs

        public static final PlacerDirective SSI_BalanceSLRs
        Partition across SLRs to balance number of cells between SLRs.

      • SSI_HighUtilSLRs

        public static final PlacerDirective SSI_HighUtilSLRs
        Direct the placer to attempt to place logic closer together in each SLR.

      • RuntimeOptimized

        public static final PlacerDirective RuntimeOptimized
        Run fewest iterations, trade higher design performance for faster runtime.

      • Quick

        public static final PlacerDirective Quick
        Absolute, fastest runtime, non-timing-driven, performs the minimum required placement for a legal design.

      • Default

        public static final PlacerDirective Default
        Run place_design with default settings.
